/*
:name: signed_one_bit_cmp
:type: equiv
:verilog_top: signed_one_bit_cmp.p
:pyrope_top: p
*/

// Ordered comparison of a 1-bit SIGNED value. `signed(x#[3])` reinterprets the
// u1 bit as s1 = {-1, 0}; a set bit is -1, so `signed(x#[3]) < 0` == x[3]. The
// W==1 signed ordered-compare gap (LT/encode signedness + cgen signed reg) is
// FIXED, so both directions now PROVE:
//   * forward prp-equiv: cgen emits `reg signed; b = (sext < 'sb0)`, yosys
//     lgcheck proves it equals the golden `assign b = x[3]`.
//   * reverse prp-v2prp: cvc5 proves the slang-reconstructed Pyrope equivalent.
// The golden .v module is the escaped full name `\signed_one_bit_cmp.p ` to
// match the :verilog_top: header (the filename.func convention, like trivial_if.v).
pub comb p(x:u8) -> (b:bool) {
  b = signed(x#[3]) < 0
}
